body:
This is beyond stupid, and should be considered a gamebreaking bug for Teemo players. 

&quot;Oh, I see that virtually every single Teemo player puts strategic shrooms in bushes&quot;
&quot;Let&#039;s also implement a feature that will cause wards, which are virtually always used in bushes, to cause some after effect no one even pays attention to, but will destroy Teemo&#039;s shrooms&quot;

Really starting to hate that Riot will take a champion out of the pool for a quick fix if it is a champion that is often used by professionals, but will decide to just &quot;let it ride&quot; if it&#039;s someone who actually needs attention due to a gamebreaking bug.

"Oh, it is just affecting Teemo? He isn't played in any professional tournament, so we can just ignore it! :)"
